arm64: NXP SDK compat shims (ioremap_cache_ns + pgprot_cached_ns)

The lf-6.6.y SDK calls two NXP-private arm64 helpers absent from mainline:

  - ioremap_cache_ns()   in bman_driver.c:194, qman_driver.c:451
  - pgprot_cached_ns()   in fsl_usdpaa.c:829

NXP defines both via PROT_NORMAL_NS / PTE_NS (Non-Secure TLB attr), which
mainline lacks.  On stock linux-6.6.137 each call is an implicit-decl and
dies under -Werror.

Aliases:
  - ioremap_cache_ns(addr, size) -> ioremap_cache(addr, size).  The two
    attr sets differ only in the NS bit; on this SoC running in EL2 the
    portals never traverse secure-world.  The cacheable mapping is what
    the older 5.4 SDK overlay used before NXP added the _ns variant.
  - pgprot_cached_ns(prot) -> identity.  vma->vm_page_prot is already
    PROT_DEFAULT cacheable from remap_pfn_range() on normal memory; the
    SDK callsite just wants to keep that attribute.

--- a/arch/arm64/include/asm/io.h
+++ b/arch/arm64/include/asm/io.h
@@ -162,6 +162,12 @@
 #include <asm-generic/io.h>
 
 #define ioremap_cache ioremap_cache
+/* NXP SDK compat: lf-6.x defines this with PROT_NORMAL_NS; mainline lacks it.
+ * Cacheable mapping is a strict superset for our portal-CE use; alias it. */
+#define ioremap_cache_ns(addr, size) ioremap_cache((addr), (size))
+/* NXP SDK compat: pgprot_cached_ns aliases to identity; vma->vm_page_prot
+ * is already PROT_DEFAULT cacheable from remap_pfn_range(). */
+#define pgprot_cached_ns(prot) (prot)
 static inline void __iomem *ioremap_cache(phys_addr_t addr, size_t size)
 {
 	if (pfn_is_map_memory(__phys_to_pfn(addr)))
